results.name: Patta 20th Anniversary Chlorophyll
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 Patta 20th Anniversary Chlorophyll
results.description:
Celebrate 20 years of Patta with the Nike Air Max 1 Patta 20th Anniversary Chlorophyll, which released in 2024 and pays homage to the 5th anniversary model which released in 2009.

This sneaker features a grey, white, and green upper with a white midsole. This sneaker is highly coveted by sneakerheads due to it's similarly to the 5th anniversary model that released in 2009, that has similar color blocking. The Patta and Air Max branding can be seen on the tongue in white and green stitching. We love this sneaker due to its bold colors and OG references, making for a classic sneaker that you truly cannot go wrong with.

The Nike Air Max 1 Patta 20th Anniversary Chlorophyll released on September 13th, 2024, for a retail price of $160.

results.name: Triple Black
results.title: Nike Air VaporMax Plus Triple Black
results.description:
The Nike VaporMax Plus Triple Black is a combination of the Air Max Plus series, which was released in 1998, and the VaporMax series.

The Nike VaporMax Plus Triple Black has an upper construction of neoprene, true to the iconic look of the Nike Air Max Plus. The length of the Air Max sole extends through the entire sneaker. The tongue displays the Air Vapor Max Plus branding, and the VM logo is seen on the heel. The VM logo provides contrast through its yellow, white, and red colors. The heel is reminiscent of the Tuned Air Logo from 1998. Short white stripes run through the upper part of the Nike VaporMax complete the design.

The Nike Air VaporMax Plus Triple Black released in January of 2018 and retailed for $190.

results.name: Triple White Wolf Grey
results.title: Nike Air Max 97 Triple White Wolf Grey
results.description: This Nike Air Max 97 "OG" edition comes in a white, wolf grey and black colorway. Made to commemorate the 30th Anniversary of the classic Air Max silhouette. This pair sports a clean all-white upper and sole with the only hits of color coming from the grey branding. They were one of three colorways that dropped alongside each other. The release date was August 1st, 2017 where they retailed for $160 in men's sizes. This Nike Air Max 97 "OG" re-released in May of 2023. Fans of the Air Max 97 were very pleased with this colorway and it quickly became a must-have. Perfect for everyday use, you can never go wrong with an a white pair of kicks. If you're in need of a pair, hit up the marketplace to buy them. Those looking to sell can do so online today.

results.name: Triple Black
results.title: Nike Air Max Plus Triple Black
results.description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Triple Black is an all-black rendition of the Nike Air Max Plus. Released ahead of the 20th anniversary of the Nike Air Max Plus, this shoe features a breathable synthetic upper with closed mesh inserts as well as edgy TPU ribbing, an external toe cap, a textured ankle strip, and a low mudguard. It also features a lightweight midsole with Tuned Air technology and a Max Air sole unit.

The Nike Air Max Plus Triple Black was released on December 20, 2017. At the time of its release, it retailed for $150.

results.name: White
results.title: Nike Air VaporMax Plus White
results.description:
The Nike Air VaporMax Plus White features an off-white neoprene upper with a white TPU cage and gray Swooshes. From there, the shoe's signature translucent outsole and VM branding on the heel complete the design.

The Nike Air VaporMax Plus White released in February of 2018 and retailed for $190.

results.name: Reverse Duck Camo
results.title: Nike Air Max 90 Reverse Duck Camo
results.description:
Nike celebrated Air Max Day 2020 by releasing the Nike Air Max 90 Reverse Duck Camo. This colorway is a fresh take on the classic Atmos Air Max 90 design that debuted in 2013.

This Air Max 90 consisted of an Infrared mesh upper with a Duck Camo mudguard and black quarter panels. A Nike Air branded heel tab, white midsole, and a mixed infrared and black outsole completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 90 Reverse Duck Camo released in March of 2020 and retailed for $140. The Nike Air Max 90 Reverse Duck Camo re-released in September of 2024.

results.name: Big Bubble Air Max Day (2024)
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Air Max Day (2024)
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Air Max Day (2024) is a special-edition sneaker that was released to celebrate Air Max Day.

The sneaker boasts a white mesh construction with suede overlays in Royal Blue and Sail. Unlike other Nike Air Max 1 models released as part of Air Max Day, the "Big Bubble Air Max Day" iteration features a Volt midsole that catches the eye. The tongue’s inner lining also showcases a panel of Volt synthetic material. The oversized window in the heel displays visible Air Max units and four circular cut outs.

Something our StockX experts like is the ‘3.26’ on the tongue’s logo tag. It represents the date of Air Max Day and comes in chunky Blue Volt letters. The Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Air Max Day (2024) was launched on March 26th, 2024, and sold for $150.

results.name: Black White (2024)
results.title: Nike Air DT Max '96 Black White (2024)
results.description:
The Nike Air DT Max '96 Black White (2024) is a shoe designed as a revival of the original design from the 1990s.

This iteration of the Nike Air DT Max ‘96 is constructed with a white leather base for the upper. The upper is covered with a black leather overlay that looks like it’s dripping from the top in streaks down the white midsole and into the outsole. Black also forms the toe cap, and on the lateral side, the black streaks have perforations that reveal a Varsity Maize yellow color underneath. Small yellow Nike swooshes also appear on each side of the ankle, and a black strap over the laces contains a white Nike swoosh. The heel contains a yellow Swoosh and the word "AIR," while the tongue also features branding elements. The white wavy outsole contains a visible Air DT Max unit in the heel.

What we like most about this particular sneaker is the way the black overlays look like they’re dripping down the shoe’s upper. The Nike Air DT Max '96 Black White (2024) was released on June 14, 2024, for $170.

results.name: Concepts Mellow
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 SP Concepts Mellow
results.description:
PLEASE NOTE: Print Patterns May Vary. In collaboration with Boston-based boutique Concepts, the Nike Air Max 1 SP Concepts Mellow pays homage to '60s and '70s youth culture with its fabrication and palette. It is constructed with a medley of bleached denim, ripstop canvas, red velour, and bandana materials, each contrasting one another. The embroidered "flower power" Swoosh nods to common clothing design themes of the 1970s. At the base, a speckled Air Max sole completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 1 SP Concepts Mellow released in March of 2022 and retailed for $170.

results.name: Leather Triple White
results.title: Nike Air Max 90 Leather Triple White
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Leather Triple White 2020 takes on a 1990 original design, and is covered in an all-white finish.
​
​The sneaker is constructed of white TPU eyelets, a mesh upper with stitched leather overlays, a waffle-tread rubber outsole for traction and an Air-infused midsole for cushioning. Further, it displays Air Max units on both medial sides with a padded tongue panel printed with a Nike Swoosh emblem. Additionally, this Air Max Triple version has printed Nike branding on its heel.
​
​The Nike Air Max 90 Leather Triple White 2020 debuted on July 28th, 2020, and retailed at $130.

results.name: White Black
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 White Black
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 1 White Black paints the Air Max 1 silhouette in a contrasting colorway of white, black, and Pure Platinum.

Like the original Air Max 1 from 1987, the "White Black" version was designed with comfort in mind and includes design elements that pay tribute to the original. For example, the sneaker features wavy mudguards and overlapping overlays. The waffle design on the rubber outsole is another feature that pays homage to the sneaker’s running roots. It also provides traction without adding bulky lugs. While white is the base’s dominant color, the leather overlays come in Pure Platinum and the mudguard is black. Notable branding elements include the Swooshes on the side panels and the retro-inspired logo tag on the tongue.

Our StockX experts appreciate the transparent windows in the heel, which allow you to see the Air Max unit. The Nike Air Max 1 White Black was released on January 4th, 2024, and retailed at $140.

results.name: Black Anthracite
results.title: Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite
results.description:
The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite was designed with both utility and sustainability in mind.

The uppers are made out of stretchy and breathable Flyknit fabric, and they are adorned by the brand’s iconic Swoosh symbol. There is also a classic Nike symbol that is featured on the insoles. The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite is made out of 40% recycled content by weight. The Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite has two cushioning units that are sizable yet sleek. These units sit across recycled rubber outsoles and are bolstered by recycled TPU clips.

What our experts like the most in the Nike Air VaporMax 2021 FK Black Anthracite is its sleek design and total black colorway. The midsole and outsole complete the Nike sneaker making it one of the classics and recognizable designs of the Nike Air lines. The sneaker was first released in June of 2021 at a starting price of $200.

results.name: Canyon Gold Deep Ocean (Women's)
results.title: Nike Air Max Sunder Canyon Gold Deep Ocean (Women's)
results.description:
The Nike Air Max Sunder Canyon Gold Deep Ocean (Women's) is a relaunch of the original sneaker from 1999 that maintains many retro elements.

At the Canyon Gold Deep Ocean (Women's) Nike Air Max Sunder, A zip fastening secures the polyurethane shroud and features a large circular pull tab as well as black-tone hardware. Two pull tabs help you put on or take off the shoe, while the rubber outsole houses responsive, visible Air Max units in the heel. In addition, Nike Air cushioning in the forefoot provides bounce. What makes this sneaker stand out is the ultra-bright colorway of Canyon Gold, Deep Ocean, and Speed Yellow with accents in Light Smoke Gray. The orange and yellow hues fade across the shroud and add pops of color to the outsole.

Our experts like the nod to Nike’s offices around the world – the numbers ‘6453’ that are revealed beneath the zip fastening. The women’s size Nike Air Max Sunder Canyon Gold Deep Ocean (Women's) was released on July 11, 2024, and sold for $180.

results.name: Bacon (2021)
results.title: Nike Air Max 90 NRG Bacon (2021)
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 90 Bacon is still one of the most highly sought-after Air Max runners of all time. So much so that Nike brought back the 2004 design to celebrate Air Max Day in 2021. It is not often that Nike retros collaborations, while most rarely resurface. But with its continuously growing fan base and pleas from Air Max fans to revive the 16-year-old colorway, Nike brought back the sneaker in its OG form.

The Nike Air Max 90 Bacon returns with all of the design qualities from the 2004 collaboration with Dave’s Quality Meat’s creator, David Ortiz. Mimicking the different shades of colors that appear from raw bacon, the sneaker is composed of various shades of brown, red, pink, and off-white. With a combination of suede, tumbled leather, and mesh, this Air Max 90 brings a luxe feel to the traditional 1990 model.

The Nike Air Max 90 Bacon released in March of 2021 for $140.

results.name: Travis Scott Cactus Jack Saturn Gold
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Saturn Gold
results.description:
In collaboration with Travis Scott's record label Cactus Jack, the Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Saturn Gold pays homage to outdoor exploration and the Nike ACG Pocket Knife hiking shoe. It boasts a light yellow layered mesh upper with matching Durabuck overlays and reversed Swoosh logos. A drawstring Gillie lacing system nods to common features on trail runners. At the base, a yellowed sole with a cloudy Air unit adds the finishing touch.

The Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Saturn Gold released in May of 2022 and retailed for $150.

results.name: Summit White Concord
results.title: Nike Air Max 180 Summit White Concord
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 180 Summit White Concord is a reissue of the iconic Air Max 180 designed by Tinker Hatfield in 1991. In comparison to other reissues, this shoe more closely resembles the OG sneaker with its understated design and retro-inspired colorway.

The Summit White Concord Nike Air Max 180 is outfitted with a Summit White base and accents in metallic gold and Bright Concord. Grape-purple Concord appears on the midsole wedge, the outsole, the collar, and the flat tongue, while metallic gold stands out on the Swoosh logos and the "NIKE AIR" embroidery on the heel. The upper construction combines suede and mesh, drawing inspiration from the original shoe. However, the sneaker includes several modern upgrades, including a larger 180-degree Air unit underfoot.

Our experts like the way the gold Swoosh pays tribute to Team USA’s men’s basketball victory at the 1992 Barcelona Olympics. The Nike Air Max 180 Summit White Concord was released on August 7, 2024, and sold for $150.

results.name: Origins Waterway
results.title: Nike Air Max Plus Origins Waterway
results.description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Origins Waterway applies a serene palm tree pattern to the Air Max Plus to celebrate Sean McDowell, the designer behind this iconic sneaker.​
​
The palm trees represent one of the natural elements that inspired Sean McDowell while he created the Air Max. Although other versions of the Air Max Plus feature sunset colors, the "Origins Waterway" variation boasts a white background with palm trees printed in Waterway and Fiberglass. This gives the sneaker a tonally cooler appearance than other models. The upper is made of a lightweight synthetic mesh with wavy lines winding across the exterior in a silver-like hue. The chunky midsole displays visible Air Max units in the heel and forefoot. In terms of branding, a yellow logo on the heel displays ‘TN AIR’ and the tongue houses a Swoosh and ‘AIR’ lettering.
​​
​Our experts at StockX like the way the lines across the upper mimic wind blowing through the palm trees. The Nike Air Max Plus Origins Waterway was released on October 31st, 2023, and retailed at $190.

results.name: White
results.title: Nike Air Max Plus White
results.description:
The Nike Air Max Plus White is a versatile shoe, ideal for everyday use and an active lifestyle. There is air cushioning on the heels and forefront, allowing for full-length cushion and support. The ankles are also well-supported. The wavy design lines are complemented with the plastic accents and breathable mesh on the upper of the shoe. The shoe also features colored air pods to provide a touch of contrast, and the all-white color of the Nike Air Plus White gives it a clean look.

The Nike Air Max Plus White was released in January of 2019 for $150.

results.name: Triple Black
results.title: Nike Air Max 270 Triple Black
results.description:
Crafted from a breathable mesh and canvas upper, the Nike Air Max 270 Triple Black now features 270 degrees of visible Air for extra comfort. Drawing inspiration from the sleek Air Max 180, the Nike Air Max 270 Triple Black features a slip-in bootie construction to deliver a great fit. The sneaker boasts a Max Air unit with 270 degrees of air encapsulated in the heel. The sneaker utilizes lightweight and soft neoprene across the upper to ensure airflow to the foot.

The Nike Air Max 270 Triple Black was released in March 2018 at a retail price of $160.

results.name: Triple Black
results.title: Nike Air Max 2017 Triple Black
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 2017 Triple Black was created for individuals that are active. This model can be worn for everyday walking and more intense exercise.

This model has a cushioned, supportive sole that was designed with support and comfort in mind. The upper body of the shoe, like the sole, is completely black, and made out of a mixture of leather and mesh. The Nike swoosh symbol can be subtly found in the lower part of the shoe near the heel.

The Nike Air Max 2017 Triple Black had a starting release date of August 2017. This model was released with a starting retail price of $160.

results.name: CLOT Kiss of Death (2021)
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 CLOT Kiss of Death (2021)
results.description:
Nike and long-time collaborator, CLOT, reissued their Nike Air Max 1 CLOT Kiss Of Death in 2021. The sneaker debuted in 2006 and now the original pair is reselling for over $1,000 on StockX. Bringing back the collab in its original design answers the prayers of many Air Max fans that were unable to get their hands on the pair 15 years ago and in the years since.

For CLOT founder, Edison Chen, the sole mission of his work with Nike is to bridge Eastern and Western cultures through design and storytelling based on Chinese traditions. The Nike Air Max 1 CLOT Kiss Of Death fulfills this mission by mixing Nike’s innovative designs with Chinese philosophies on medicine, specifically foot pressure points. The upper is composed of translucent materials, making feet the focal point. Following the translucent theme, the shoe also features an icy-blue outsole with a printed diagram showing the pressure points on the foot. The shoe also incorporates some luxe details, such as faux snakeskin on the Swoosh and ostrich texture on the collar.

The Nike Air Max 1 CLOT Kiss Of Death released in March of 2021 for $150.

results.name: White Black (Women's)
results.title: Nike Air Max 270 White Black (Women's)
results.description:
Among the variants of Nike Air Max 270, the women’s Nike Air Max 270 White Black is one of those that continues to attract the highest number of sales since its release.

The upper part of the shoe comprises of white and black woven and synthetic fabric. The elongated shoe tongue underneath the white cotton shoelaces is made of smooth white leather. The midsole and outsole of Nike Air Max 270 White Black (women) are both made of white rubber, with the outsole featuring bouncy properties.

The release date of the Nike Air Max 270 White Black (women) was on February 3, 2018. The shoe debuted at a price of $150.

results.name: Big Bubble Sport Red
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Sport Red
results.description:
Nike is celebrating Air Max Day in 2023 by bringing back an original Air Max design, with the release of the Nike Air Max 1 ‘86 Big Bubble Sport Red. The Big Bubble pays homage to the original design of the Nike Air Max 1, which featured a bigger air unit.

The Air Max 1 ‘86 Big Bubble released as Nikes premier Air Max Day release in 2023. The sneakers are constructed using grey synthetic nubuck, white mesh and red synthetic suede across the uppers and a large air unit on the midsole. Nike used Sport Red branding on the tongue and heel of the sneaker.

The Nike Air Max 1 ‘86 Big Bubble Sport Red released March 26, 2023, with a retail price of $150.

results.name: Patta Waves Rush Maroon (with Bracelet)
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Rush Maroon (with Bracelet)
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Noise Rush Maroon features a grey mesh upper with smooth maroon leather overlays and wave-shaped mudguards. A yellowed Air sole with a brown outsole adds the finishing touches.

The Nike Air Max 1 Patta Waves Noise Rush Maroon released in November of 2021 and retailed for $160.

results.name: Black White Grey
results.title: Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey
results.description:
The Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey is a comfortable yet flexible shoe that provides all of the best athletic qualities while still being stylish.

The Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey provides an ample amount of heel support and has a particularly cushioned sole. Splashes of pink and green appear in contrast to the black, white, and grey pattern that makes up a majority of the shoe. The upper part of the Nike Air Max Correlate Black White Grey molds to the foot, helping to provide support and protection while still remaining comfortable.

First released in May 2022 at a starting price of $155.

results.name: White Grey Fog
results.title: Nike Air Max 95 Essential White Grey Fog
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 95 Essential White Grey Fog is white with grey fog accents. The footwear is designed with a mesh upper, reinforced with full-grain leather overlays. It has white, fast-lace laces and can be slipped on. Its sole is flat with a thickness of 4cm. The footwear insoles are non-removable with a textile lining. Themidsole is made of foam. The footwear further has visible Nike Air cushioning. A small Nike Swoosh is on one side of the heel.
​
The Nike Air Max 95 Essential White Grey Fog was released in November 2021 at a retail price of $170.

results.name: Travis Scott Cactus Jack Baroque Brown
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Baroque Brown
results.description:
In collaboration with Travis Scott's record label Cactus Jack, the Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Brown draws inspiration from the Nike ACG Pocket Knife hiking shoe. It features a layered mesh upper with tonal-brown Durabuck overlays and reversed Swoosh logos. A drawstring Gillie lacing system nods to common features on trail runners. At the base, a yellowed sole with a cloudy Air unit completes the design.

The Nike Air Max 1 Travis Scott Cactus Jack Brown released in May of 2022 and retailed for $150.

results.name: Triple Black
results.title: Nike Air Max 95 Essential Triple Black
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 95 Essential Triple Black 2020/2023 was originally unveiled as one of Nike’s Nike Air Max 95 model sneakers in January 2020.

The Nike Air Max 95 Essential Triple Black 2020/2023 is dressed in a black-on-black colorway. The sneaker features a black mesh-constructed upper on top of a black leather base. The black tongue’s top features an "air max" labeling detail. Completing the design is the black rubber sole with Air Max units fitted within the heel and forefoot for extra comfort. The black rubber outsole is patterned for maximum traction.

During its initial unveiling in January 2020, Nike Air Max 95 Triple Black 2020 retailed at $170.

results.name: 25th Anniversary
results.title: Nike Air Max Plus 25th Anniversary
results.description:
The Nike Air Max Plus 25th Anniversary was released to celebrate the 25th anniversary of the original Nike Air Max Plus. This commemorative sneaker features a color scheme and design that pay tribute to prominent Air Max colorways, including "Palm," "Hyper Blue," "Fireberry," and "Sanguine."

Like other Air Max Plus models, the 25th Anniversary variation boasts a polyurethane midsole with a midfoot shank inspired by the curve of a whale’s tail. The upper is made of breathable mesh, displaying a color gradient that fades from light blue to Varsity Blue to purple to red with a palm pattern. Each color represents one of the famous Air Max colorways. A TPU cage supports the soft upper and mimics the sway of palm trees moving in the breeze.

Our StockX experts like visible Air Max units in the chunky midsole. The Nike Air Max Plus 25th Anniversary was released on November 9, 2023, and retailed at $185.

results.name: Shima Shima (2023)
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 Premium Shima Shima (2023)
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 1 Premium Shima Shima 2023 is part of the Japanese-inspired line of sneakers that arrives in a Summit White/​Plum Eclipse-Wolf Grey-White Siren Red colorway.
​
The Nike Air Max 1 Premium Shima Shima 2023's tongue tag showcases the words ""Shima Shima"" in Japanese, with the inner lining adorned with a distinctive striped pattern. The midsole is white, featuring a visible Air unit in the heel. Meanwhile, Nike matches gray and brown shades on the rubber outsole. The upper is constructed with an all-premium leather with grey quarter panels over a white base, while Swooshes and the mudguard appear in dark brown. The base features Plum Eclipse, while the Nike Air branding appears on the mudguards, Swooshes, and laces.
​
Our experts think the standout features of the Nike Air Max 1 Premium Shima Shima 2023 are the striped liner and the Japanese-themed tongue tags. The The Nike Air Max 1 Premium Shima Shima 2023 was released on March 10th, 2023, at a retail price of $160.

results.name: Big Bubble Royal (Women's)
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Royal (Women's)
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Royal Women's sneaker is a meticulous recreation of a legendary design, reviving the classic with a colorway that blends white, royal blue, neutral grey, and black. This edition pays tribute to the original Air Max 1's groundbreaking introduction, offering enthusiasts a taste of the past with the distinctive "Big Bubble" feature that set the sneaker world ablaze. Designed for those who appreciates the fusion of heritage and contemporary style, this sneaker is a nod to the pioneers of sneaker culture.

What sets the '86 OG Big Bubble version apart is the enhanced air unit in the heel, providing a glimpse into the sneaker innovation that revolutionized comfort and aesthetics in athletic footwear. This detail, coupled with the iconic colorway, makes the sneaker not only a piece of history but also a testament to Nike's enduring influence on sportswear design. The blend of royal blue and neutral tones on a pristine white base offers a look that's both fresh and timeless, appealing to a wide range of tastes and styles.

Released on March 22, 2024, for $150, the Nike Air Max 1 '86 OG Big Bubble Royal quickly ascended to must-have status among sneaker aficionados and style mavens. Its launch is celebrated for reintroducing a classic silhouette with its original specifications to a new generation. It's a piece of athletic history, a homage to innovation, and a beacon of timeless style.

results.name: Black Racer Blue
results.title: Nike Air Max Plus Premium Black Racer Blue
results.description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Premium Black Racer Blue displays a color gradient from black to Phantom to Racer Blue and the shoe’s signature TPU overlays.

The Black Racer Bule Nike Air Max Plus Premium was inspired by nature, where the overlays take on a wavy design that emulates waves or swaying palm trees. They create the feeling of movement across the upper and support the airy mesh. Another nature-inspired element is the midfoot arch, which supports the foot and resembles a whale’s tale. Starting from the heel, the upper fades from black to Racer Blue with a genuine leather mudguard in black wrapping around the shoe. The sole unit includes visible Nike Air units that offer lightweight support and give the sneaker a technical appearance.

Our experts like the bright white Swoosh logos on the side panels. Even though they’re small, in our option, these iconic logos are all the branding the shoe needs. The Nike Air Max Plus Premium Black Racer Blue was released on July 14, 2024, and sold for $190.

results.name: Sunset (2024)
results.title: Nike Air Max Plus Sunset (2024)
results.description:
The Nike Air Max Plus Sunset (2024) is a special-edition of the "Sunset" colorway, which has been released numerous times over the years throughout the history of the Nike Air Max Plus.

The wave-like upper has TPU overlays that resembles waves in the sea as the sun sets. Aiming to mimic and capture all phases of a sunset, you’ll notice how the colors gradient from a bright Ceramic Yellow in the toe area all the way to a deep dark pimento in the heel area. Together with other colors such as black, resin, and white, the effect is nothing less than spectacular. On the quarter side panels, you’ll spot small red Nike Swooshes, while iconic Tuned Air (TN) logos sit on the heel, on the insole, and underfoot in the middle of the outsole.

What our experts love about this shoe is how the Air Units complement the idea of a sunset, the orange color peeking through adds to the overall aesthetic. When it was released on July 3, 2024, the Nike Air Max Plus Sunset (2024) had a $180 price tag.

results.name: Olympic
results.title: Nike Air Max 1 Olympic
results.description:
Released ahead of the 2024 Paris Olympics, the Nike Air Max 1 Olympic decks out the Air Max 1 silhouette with details inspired by the Olympic Games.

The Olympic Nike Air Max 1 embodies the spirit of Team USA, with a white base and patriotic accents in obsidian-blue and red. A metallic-gold Swoosh logo graces the side panel and represents the drive to achieve Olympic gold. Classic color blocking on the upper pays homage to the original Air Max 1, while the obsidian mudguard takes notes from the OG Obsidian colorway. The upper construction consists of a mesh base with Light Smoke Grey overlays near the rear and midfoot. Pops of red stand out on the eyelets, the tongue’s logo tag, and the NIKE AIR branding on the heel.

Our experts like how this sneaker subtly celebrates the 2024 Olympics and Team USA through colors instead of motifs or bold lettering. The Nike Air Max 1 Olympic was released on June 17, 2024, and sold for $150.

results.name: Ultramarine (2024)
results.title: Nike Air Max 180 Ultramarine (2024)
results.description:
The Nike Air Max 180 Ultramarine (2024) is a stunning reissue of the classic 1991 design by Tinker Hatfield. This sneaker features a white neoprene upper with suede overlays, highlighted by vibrant ultramarine blue and solar red accents. The signature exposed Air unit adds a futuristic touch, making this sneaker both a fashion statement and a functional piece of footwear. The bold color scheme and high-quality materials ensure that this sneaker stands out in any crowd.

Since its introduction, the Air Max 180 has been celebrated for its revolutionary 180-degree Air unit, providing maximum comfort and cushioning. The Ultramarine colorway, one of the most iconic in the Air Max lineup, is known for its eye-catching design and vibrant colors. The 2024 re-release faithfully replicates the original, offering the same striking visuals and superior comfort.

Priced at $150, the Nike Air Max 180 Ultramarine (2024) was released on May 24, 2024. This sneaker is not just a piece of athletic footwear but a piece of cultural history. The Ultramarine colorway brings a fresh yet nostalgic vibe, making it a must-have for sneaker collectors and fashion enthusiasts alike. Don’t miss your chance to own this timeless classic and experience the perfect blend of style, comfort, and heritage.
